methods.capacity:
Get a hint about this cache's capacity and behavior.

:return: (int) -1 : This is an unbounded cache. 0 : This "cache" doesn't actually perform any caching. >0 : Actual
         capacity bound.
methods.getCachedString:
Convenience method to allow arbitrary CharSequence references to be used in lookup.

*Overload 1*  
  :param protoString: (io.deephaven.base.string.cache.StringCompatible) - The string-like CharSequence to look up
  :return: (StringCache.STRING_LIKE_TYPE) A cached STRING_LIKE_TYPE that corresponds to the current value of the CharSequence expressed by
           protoString
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param string: (java.lang.String) - The String to look up
  :return: (StringCache.STRING_LIKE_TYPE) A cached STRING_LIKE_TYPE that corresponds to the CharSequence expressed by string
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param charSequence: (java.lang.CharSequence) - The CharSequence to look up
  :return: (StringCache.STRING_LIKE_TYPE) A cached STRING_LIKE_TYPE that corresponds to charSequence
methods.getEmptyString: :return: (StringCache.STRING_LIKE_TYPE) A cached STRING_LIKE_TYPE that represents the empty string.
methods.getType: :return: (java.lang.Class<StringCache.STRING_LIKE_TYPE>) The type of the elements in this cache.

text: Generic caching interface for Strings and String-like CharSequences.
